svg.desc: The chart shows the proportion of unmarried children within their parents’ household by family form in 1996 and 2015. In 2015, most children, 72 percent, were still growing up in a household with married parents. This is more than 10 percent fewer than in 1996. In 2015, some 21 percent of children were growing up with a single parent and 7 percent in an unmarried partnership. In the East German larger, rural states, some 58 percent of children were living with married parents. This is far fewer than in West German larger, rural states where the figure stood at some 75 percent. In city-states, the comparable figure was just under 60 percent.

div.p:
Source: German Federal Statistical Office (2017), Results of the Microcensus 2015.
